Presenting a summery twist to the most chatpata and sought-after street snack - ✨*Mango flavoured Gol Gappe*✨ - made by yours truly! 💁‍♀️

This recipe is extra special for me as I have learnt it from my Dadi, who has always been the OG innovator in the kitchen! She made our summer holidays a lot more fun with such fusions in her traditional recipes!👵

And to help me make the perfect masala for my Gol Gappas, I have used Nutri blend from @wondercheflife .  Ab masala grind karna ho ya phir puree banani ho, isse mera kaam ho jaata hai ekdum aasan!

Highly recommend trying out this recipe at home, before we bid adieu to the King of Fruits!

Detailed recipe as below:
*Ingredients:*
For Gol Gappe ka masala:
1 tbsp dried mint leaves
1 tbsp roasted cumin seeds
1 tbsp black salt
1 tbsp amchur powder
8-10 black peppers
2 tbsp coriander seeds

For Gol Gappa pani:
1 cup mango pulp
½ cup raw mango
Handful green coriander
½ cup mint leaves
2 green chillies
½ inch ginger
¼ cup sugar
1/3 cup boondi
Ice cubes

*Method:*
1. In the Wonderchef Nutri-blend grinding jar, add dried mint leaves, black salt, roasted cumin, amchur powder, black pepper and coriander seeds and grind it into a fine powder. Gol Gappa masala is ready.
2. Now in the blending jar, add mango pulp, raw mango, mint leaves, green coriander, green chilli, ginger, sugar and ice cubes. Blend it into a smooth puree.
3. Now transfer the puree in a bowl. Add prepared Gol Gappa masala, chilled water, chopped mango. Mix it well and then add boondi and ice cubes. Mango flavoured gol gappa ka pani is ready.
4. Serve the pani with Gol gappa. Make a hole in the Gol Gappa, dip in the pani with boondi and mangoes and eat immediately.

15 Minutes Arabian bread pudding -
you can make this delicious thanda thanda dessert for summers. Everybody will love this 😍

Save the video and try it later

Follow @purna_recipes for more interesting recipes 

Ingredients -
For custard mixture –
500 Milk
2 tbsp custard powder(vanilla flavoured)
4 tbsp Milk to mix custard powder
1/3 cup condensed Milk
For Cream Mixture –
1/2 Cup chilled Fresh cream
¼ cup condensed Milk
For assembly –
Milk Bread sliced as required
3-4 almonds
1 tbsp chopped pistachio
Rose petals 

Method –
•	In a small mixing bowl, combine custard powder with milk.
•	Using a spoon, mix until the custard powder dissolves.
•	Place a small deep pot on the stove over medium heat.
•	Pour milk and bring it to a boil while stirring continuously.
•	Add ¼ cup of condensed milk.
•	Add the custard mixture you prepared earlier to the milk.
•	Stir well and cook for 4-5 minutes until the mixture thickens. Keep the custard mixture aside for later use.

Prepare The Cream Mixture
•	In a mixing bowl, add chilled fresh cream with condensed milk. Mix it well and keep aside.

Assemble The Bread Pudding

•	Take slices of white bread and cut the sides off each slice using a knife.
•	Place bread slices in a large serving dish.
•	Pour a portion of the custard mixture you prepared earlier over the bread slices. Make sure the custard mixture covers all the bread slices.
•	Now pour some of the cream over the bread slices evenly.
•	Place the remaining bread slices on top of the layers.
•	Pour the rest of the custard mixture over the bread slices and spread the cream mixture on top of the custard mixture. Make sure all the bread slices are soaked completely.

Garnish, Chill and Serve
•	Sprinkle chopped almonds and chopped pistachios over the bread pudding.
•	Refrigerate the dish for 15-20 minutes and allow the pudding to set.
•	Cut the bread slices from the pudding and enjoy the delicious Arabian bread pudding dessert!
